<HEAD>New Snow Slides Kill At Least 145 in Kashmir</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More avalanches crashed down on mountain
villages in the northern Kashmir state, killing at least 145 people
and injuring more than 100, United News of India reported today.
   The casualties in Friday's snow slides brought to at least 217
the death toll from avalanches in the mountain state since snow
storms hit March 10.
   UNI said the Friday's avalanches hit three villages in in Kargil
district, about 90 miles northeast of the state's capital of
Srinagar.
   The agency said senior government officials made aerial survey
of the affected areas and relief operations were under way. It said
roads to many of the affected villages were blocked by snow.
</TEXT>
