<2ND_LINE>PM-Washington in Brief,450</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bill Would Boost Nuclear Accident Insurance Pool</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nationwide pool of insurance funds to be
tapped in the event of an accident at a nuclear reactor or related
facility would grow from $700 million to more than $7 billion under
legislation approved by the Senate.
   The proposal, approved by Senate voice vote Friday, is part of
legislation providing a 20-year extension of the Price-Anderson
Act. The bill now goes back to the House, which approved a slightly
different version last July.
   Under current provisions of the Price-Anderson Act, the pool
could pay up to $700 million to compensate victims if the accident
involved a commercial nuclear power plant, and up to $500 million
if it involved a government-owned facility. Both the House and
Senate versions of the renewal legislation would boost the amount
in both cases to more than $7 billion.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Aliens Given Extra 60 Days To File Back-up Documents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government is giving illegal aliens who
want to file for amnesty an extra 60 days to come up with the
documents to support their applications for legalization.
   Under the change announced Friday, the application deadline of
May 4 still will stand, but amnesty seekers who file in the final
month before then will have until July 5 to produce back-up
documentation and medical data.
   ``If any of you have ever filed your income tax on the night of
the 14th of April, there's usually one document or one fact you
don't get,'' Attorney General Edwin Meese III told reporters at an
immigration office in Arlington, Va. ``We want to be sure that
doesn't stop anybody from this program.''
   Just over 1 million amnesty applications have been filed, and
although a last-minute surge is anticipated, the volume of requests
is likely to fall far below the 2 million estimated as recently as
January by Alan Nelson, commissioner of the U.S. Immigration and
Naturalization Service.
</TEXT>
