<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0411</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Northeast Gets Scattered Snow; South Gets Rain</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Light snow was scattered over parts of the East and Midwest
today, while rain stretched from Florida to Mississippi.
   Snow fell on Michigan and parts of Pennsylvania, Ohio, West
Virginia and Maryland. Forecasters posted snow advisories today for
parts of North Carolina, Maryland and New England.
   Snow changed to rain and extended across Virginia and the
Carolinas into eastern Tennessee. Rain also fell across Florida,
southern Mississippi and southwest Alabama.
   About 1 inch of snow and ice covered the higher elevations of
the Smokey Mountains in eastern Tennessee Friday night.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms across
southern and central Florida; rain along the remainder of the
southern Atlantic Coast; snow over the Great Lakes and the Ohio
Valley; scattered snow or flurries from New England into the
central Appalachians; rain over western Washington state and
northwest Oregon; sunny skies from California to the lower
Mississippi Valley; strong, gusty winds near the eastern slopes of
the northern Rockies and along the coast of the Carolinas.
   Highs were expected to be in the 50s or 60s for much of the
nation; teens and 20s from North Dakota across the Great Lakes
region; 30s and 40s from the lower and middle Missouri Valley to
the northern Atlantic Coast; 40s in the Tennessee Valley and the
southern Appalachians; and 70s and 80s from California across the
desert Southwest and over south Florida.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 14
degrees at International Falls, Minn., to 74 degrees at Miami,
Homestead and Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 40 cloudy; Boston 35 cloudy; Buffalo 29 snow;
Charleston, S.C. 49 cloudy; Cincinnati 29 foggy; Cleveland 31
partly cloudy; Detroit 27 fair; Miami 74 partly cloudy; New York 38
cloudy; Philadelphia 37 cloudy; Pittsburgh 27 foggy; Portland,
Maine. 31 fair; Washington 40 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 33 partly cloudy; Chicago 28 fair;
Dallas-Fort Worth 34 fair; Denver 29 fair; Des Moines 25 fair;
Indianapolis 28 fair; Kansas City 32 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul
24 fair; Nashville 32 fair; New Orleans 44 windy; St. Louis 26 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 36 fair; Anchorage 28 fair; Las Vegas 48
fair; Los Angeles 61 fair; Phoenix 60 fair; Salt Lake City 31 fair;
San Diego 59 fair; San Francisco 50 fair; Seattle 50 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 30 fair; Toronto 25 snow.
</TEXT>
