<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Rain     03-19 0101</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Rain,0103</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>100 Injured in Rain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy wind and rain lashed the
Bangladesh capital of Dhaka, flattening houses, uprooting trees and
plunging the city of 4 million into darkness, police said Saturday.
   At least 100 people were reported injured in the storm, which
hit late Friday, hospital officials said. Doctors said that 10
people were in critical condition.
   Police said the storm, with winds as high as 36 mph, ripped
through the city. Hardest hit were suburban areas, where mud and
straw huts collapsed, they said.
   Efforts were under way to restore electricity and telephone
services.
</TEXT>
