<FILEID>AP-NR-03-19-88 1206EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ArmedFashion     03-19 0334</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Armed Fashion,0342</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Firearm Fashions On Parade in Miami</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto MH2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the woman who wants that `dressed to kill'
look, fashion accessories that conceal even the bulkiest firearm
are being modeled at the Bing Bang Boom gun show this weekend.
   ``This could only happen in Miami,'' said Ron Campos, who spent
several hours Friday testing some of the weapons at the Radisson
Centre show. ``Where else would you find a fashion show on how to
wear a concealed weapon?''
   The purpose of Friday's runway show and fashion displays
throughout the weekend is to attract women into the gun market,
said promoter Ted Walker, who is also spokesman for The Shotgun
News, a Nebraska trade magazine for gun enthusiasts.
   ``What we're trying to do is show the contemporary woman that
she can carry a concealed weapon and still look good,'' he said.
   One model wore a hair bow with a holster in it. Others displayed
gun-concealing purses and bras.
   Cindy McCall modeled several lines of handbags that hide a
pistol in a secret compartment.
   If you are accosted, she said, all you need to do is slip your
hand through the Velcro panel in the back of the purse, grab the
trigger and blast. The handbag is destroyed, but what is a $100
accessory when your life is at stake?
   ``Until I found these handbags, I would not carry a weapon with
me,'' Ms. McCall said. ``When I found these, I said to myself,
`Somebody finally did something that makes sense for women.'''
   The fashion show was narrated by Charlene Meriedy, who described
a horizontal shoulder holster as ``the perfect accessory for the
business women of the '80s.'' The holster is generally worn under a
jacket.
   Some 75 firearms fans applauded as the models walked by.
   Some of the gun dealers went along with the theme of the fashion
show by offering what they called ``Sweetheart Specials,'' such as
a .22-caliber Jennings pistol that can fit readily into a purse.
</TEXT>
