<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Obit-Goralski     03-19 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Goralski,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former NBC Correspondent Robert Goralski Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert Goralski, a longtime correspondent for
NBC News, has died of cancer at age 60, a friend said Saturday.
   Charles Quinn, who worked with Goralski at NBC and, in recent
years, at the American Petroleum Institute, said Goralski died
Friday at his home in suburban McLean, Va.
   When at NBC, Goralski spent several tours covering the Vietnam
War. He also covered the Middle East War of 1967 and reported from
the White House, the Pentagon and the State Department at various
stages of his career.
   Goralski left NBC in 1975 to join the Gulf Oil Corp. as public
relations director. For the last several years, he was a senior
adviser to API, a trade association for the oil industry.
   Goralski is survived by his wife, Margaret, and three children,
adults.
</TEXT>
