<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Postal Instant Press Inc., the nation's
largest franchiser of printing centers, said Friday a
management-led offer to buy the company has expired and it is
negotiating to be acquired by another suitor for a higher price.
   The company said it received the new offer of $17.50 per share,
