<TEXT>
   An investor group led by the chairman of
AFG Industries Inc. Friday revised its takeover bid for AFG to
offer all cash instead of a combination of cash and securities. The
overall value of the offered remained the same at $940 million.
   AFG, based in Irvine, is one of the largest flat-glass
manufacturers in North America.
   Under the amended offer, Clarity Industries Corp., headed by AFG
Chairman R.D. Hubbard, is offering $33 per share in cash for AFG's
28.5 million shares. Previously, Clarity had offered cash for 94
percent of the stock and preferred stock valued at $33 per share
for the remainder.
   The revised offer is to expire April 1.
   Clarity launched its takeover bid late last month. It was
upstaged early this month when the New York investment firm
Forstmann Little & Co. indicated it may be willing to top Hubbard's
offer.
   That sparked speculation that drove AFG's stock up, but a week
ago Forstmann said it had decided not to make an offer after
studying confidential information provided by AFG.
